{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So somebody always got off the bed, and older person, and showed me how to do it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But eventually I did learn that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I also learned how to bandage pretty well with paper bandages.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "That was the only thing that we had.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Sometimes we would get unsorted medicine from transport.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "This way we got-- I remember-- some calcium tablets.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And my cousin gave me handfuls of calcium tablets, hoping that it might help me get in a little better shape, because I was in pretty miserable shape with all that fever and everything.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "In this hospital, we had it a little better physically than outside.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We worked at-- first of all, instead of seven people sleeping on a-- on top of cot, two of us slept in a single cot, which was a major improvement.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We did not stand roll calls, which was also not only for the fact that we didn't have to get up at 3 o'clock in the morning, but also that we didn't feel that our life is in danger every day by being selected.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "There's absolutely no question about it that if my cousin wouldn't have-- wouldn't have kept me in this hospital, I would not have survived the first selection.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I never had any extra weight.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I lost some during the first seven weeks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I lost more with the measles and the high fever.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Mengele came every single day and he inspected every room every single day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And we had to report to him as to how many prisoners-- we were not allowed to say people-- we had in each room.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
